{"id":"output_validator_failures_surface_as_unexpectedmodelbehavior","type":"gotcha","fact":"When a pydantic-ai `output_validator` raises `ModelRetry` and the model exhausts its internal retry budget, the exception surfacing in the caller is `pydantic_ai.exceptions.UnexpectedModelBehavior`, NOT `pydantic.ValidationError` or `ModelRetry`.","recommendation":"To recover from validator-driven failures (e.g. empty findings, missing fields), catch `UnexpectedModelBehavior` specifically — not `ValidationError`, not `Exception`. This is the exception class the per-stage retry wrapper in `app/agents/lead.py` matches against, and a naive `except Exception` would lose discrimination between transient model-output failures and genuine bugs.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"agent_pipeline_tdd_error_handling/iteration_02","date":"2026-05-24"}],"tags":["pydantic-ai","exceptions","retries","validators","output-validator"],"affectedFiles":["app/agents/lead.py","app/agents/researcher.py","app/agents/analyst.py","app/agents/reporter.py"],"createdAt":"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z"}
